article.description: Saunders, Harvard hold off Brown 76-74 in OT
article.headline: Saunders, Harvard hold off Brown 76-74 in OT
article.linkText: Saunders, Harvard hold off Brown 76-74 in OT
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. -- Wesley Saunders had a career-high 33 points and 10 rebounds with a key 3-pointer in overtime to help Harvard hold off Brown 76-74 on Friday night. Harvard (14-5, 4-1 Ivy) took the lead for good on Saunders' free throws with 3:04 left. He pushed the lead to five on a 3-pointer 45 seconds later. Brown (9-13, 0-5) had the ball only once with the score within one possession but Cedric Kuakumensah missed on a layup with the Bears trailing 71-68. Saunders also forced overtime when he put back his own miss with one second left in regulation, tying the game at 64. The victory keeps Harvard one-game behind league-leading Yale in advance of a showdown with the Bulldogs on Saturday. Agunwa Okolie and Jonah Travis added 11 points each for Harvard. Tavon Blackmon led Brown with 25. Kuakumensah scored 15 and Steven Spieth 12.
